==English==

===Adjective===

'''ruthless'''

# Having no [[ruth]]; [[cruel]]; [[pitiless]].
# [[Cruel]]; [[pitiless]]; [[barbarous]]; insensible to the miseries of others.
#:''"Their rage the hostile bands restrain, all but the ruthless monarch of the main."''

Origin: The biblical character Ruth was said to be full of compassion, thus those who are compassionless are "Ruth"-less

Ref. Webster's 1828 Dictionary

